article.description: Trevon Seymore had 15 points and tied a career high with eight assists, and Terry Harris Jr. added 14 points with eight rebounds to help Coppin State beat Florida A&M 70-66 Monday night.
article.headline: Seymore leads Coppin State to 70-66 win over Florida A&M
article.linkText: Seymore leads Coppin State to 70-66 win over Florida A&M
article.story: TALLAHASSEE, Fla. -- Trevon Seymore had 15 points and tied a career high with eight assists, and Terry Harris Jr. added 14 points with eight rebounds to help Coppin State beat Florida A&M 70-66 Monday night. Harris made 6 of 9 field-goal attempts. Christian Kessee added 14 points while Keith Shivers scored 12 on 6-of-11 shooting for Coppin State (4-14, 2/3 Mid-Eastern Athletic Conference). Blake Simpson grabbed a career-best 13 rebounds. The Eagles have won two in a row after losing 12 straight. Florida A&M (6-13, 2-4) missed all 11 of its first-half free-throw attempts and finished 8 of 21 from the foul line. Malcolm Bernard led the Rattlers with 16 points, eight rebounds and seven assists. Craig Bowman added 14 points, Jerran Foster scored 12, on a career-high four 3-pointers, and Isaiah Omoregie had 10 points on 5-of-9 shooting. Coppin State outrebounded FAMU 48-38.
